ia Institute of the Arts had long been in crisis, before Steven D. Lavine led it to financial prosperity and international acclaim. Today, CalArts is the cradle of many Academy Award and Pulitzer Prize winners, of Mellon and Guggenheim Fellows – a hotspot of American creativity. In personal conversations with Jörn Jacob Rohwer, Lavine tells his life story for the first time, talking about cultural politics, philanthropy, the avant-garde and Los Angeles at the centre of his life. Spurred on by self-doubts and a desire to learn from failure, he proves to be a sensitive thinker, visionary and transatlantic mediator between the worlds of art, politics and education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 4aBiografie. 4aCalArts. 4aFehlerkultur. 4aFührungsstil. 4aGespräch. 4aJ.J. Rohwer. 4aJudentum. 4aKunst. 4aKunstschule. 4aSteven D. Lavine. 4aThomas Mann House. 4aTransatlantische Beziehungen. 4aWalt Disney.  aArt.  aBiography.  aCalArts.  aConversations.  aCrisis.  aFailure.  aFoundraising.  aInterview.  aJudaism.  aJörn Jacob Rohwer.  aLavine.  aLos Angeles.  aRohwer.  aSteven D. Lavine.  aThomas Mann House.  aUS culture.  aWalt Disney.  aart school.  aresilience.  atransatlantic relations.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2021z9783110753790oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz97831107540010 cprintz978342298155340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978342298724140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783422987241423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783422987241/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978